  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Factorising a monic quadratic with negative terms</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Factorise the following quadratic expression completely:
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We want to factorise:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the coefficients.
</p>

<p>
Coefficient of \(x\) = {@mid@}
</p>

<p>
Constant term = {@const@}
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Find two numbers whose product is {@const@} and whose sum is {@mid@}.
</p>

<p>
The numbers are {@a@} and {@b@}, since:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@a@} \times {@b@} = {@const@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
-{@a@} + (-{@b@}) = {@mid@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Write the factorisation.
</p>

<p>
\[
(x - {@a@})(x - {@b@})
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
